 <div id="news_story" class="module first">
  <div id="storyHead">
 <header>
    <h1 class="headline">Microsoft watching what Valve does with "great interest"</h1>
 <div class="time"><time pubdate datetime="1380200893">September 26, 2013  6:08AM PDT</time></div>
   <div id="social_share_actions" class="social_share_actions"><script type="text/javascript">(function() {var toolbar = document.id('social_share_actions');if (toolbar) {toolbar.addClass('js_enabled');}}());</script><ul class="social_share_actions"><li class="social_share_action facebook_share_action"><a class="social_share_action facebook_share_action" href="http://dw.cbsi.com/redir?siteid=6&edid=107&onid=47&ptid=6036&ts=1381013002&contid=6414994&conttypid=9&pid=716424&prodtypid=8&asid=203058&useract=196&destURL=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.facebook.com%2Fsharer%2Fsharer.php%3Fu%3Dhttp%253A%252F%252Fwww.gamespot.com%252Fnews%252Fmicrosoft-watching-what-valve-does-with-great-interest-6414994%26t%3DMicrosoft%2520watching%2520what%2520Valve%2520does%2520with%2520%2522great%2520interest%2522" rel="popup:share nofollow">Facebook</a></li><li class="social_share_action tweet_share_action {'iframe_params':{'src':'http:\/\/platform.twitter.com\/widgets\/tweet_button.html?text=Microsoft%20watching%20what%20Valve%20does%20with%20%22great%20interest%22&url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.gamespot.com%2Fnews%2Fmicrosoft-watching-what-valve-does-with-great-interest-6414994&counturl=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.gamespot.com%2Fnews%2Fmicrosoft-watching-what-valve-does-with-great-interest-6414994&related=jwhdavison%2Cfiddlecub%2CCTWatters%2Cjusticecovert%2Csmcinnis%2CBrendanSinclair%2Cguycocker&via=GameSpot','scrolling':'no','frameborder':0,'allowTransparency':true,'style':'width:110px;height:20px;'},'tracking':'http:\/\/dw.cbsi.com\/redir?siteid=6&edid=107&onid=47&ptid=6036&ts=1381013002&contid=6414994&conttypid=9&pid=716424&prodtypid=8&asid=203058&useract=460&destURL=http%3A%2F%2Fimage.gamespotcdn.net%2Fgamespot%2Fb.gif'}"><a class="social_share_action tweet_share_action" href="http://dw.cbsi.com/redir?siteid=6&edid=107&onid=47&ptid=6036&ts=1381013002&contid=6414994&conttypid=9&pid=716424&prodtypid=8&asid=203058&useract=460&destURL=http%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fshare%3Ftext%3DMicrosoft%2520watching%2520what%2520Valve%2520does%2520with%2520%2522great%2520interest%2522%26url%3Dhttp%253A%252F%252Fwww.gamespot.com%252Fnews%252Fmicrosoft-watching-what-valve-does-with-great-interest-6414994%26counturl%3Dhttp%253A%252F%252Fwww.gamespot.com%252Fnews%252Fmicrosoft-watching-what-valve-does-with-great-interest-6414994%26related%3Djwhdavison%252Cfiddlecub%252CCTWatters%252Cjusticecovert%252Csmcinnis%252CBrendanSinclair%252Cguycocker%26via%3DGameSpot" rel="popup:share nofollow">Tweet</a></li><li class="social_share_action plusone_share_action"><g:plusone size="medium" callback="trackPlusOne" href="http://www.gamespot.com/news/microsoft-watching-what-valve-does-with-great-interest-6414994" rel="canonical"></g:plusone></li></ul></div>   <div class="authorByline  ">
    <a href="http://www.gamespot.com/users/eddienoteddy/"> <img src="http://image.gamespotcdn.net/gamespot/shared/authors/eddie-makuch-2_46.jpg"  class="headShotSmall" alt="Eddie Makuch" />
 </a>   <div class="wrap">
 <address>By  <a href="http://www.gamespot.com/users/eddienoteddy/">
 Eddie Makuch</a>, News Editor  </address>
   <div class="follow_buttons_wrap">
     <a class="twitter-follow-button" href="http://twitter.com/eddiemakuch" data-screen-name="EddieMakuch" data-button="blue" data-show-count="false" data-show-screen-name="false" data-lang="en">Follow @EddieMakuch</a>
    </div>
  </div>
  </div>  </header>
 </div>
  <p id="storyDeck">After Half-Life developer reveals Steam Machines, corporate vice president Phil Harrison says Valve is an "impressive company" and that "competition is good."</p>  <div class="body">
 <div class="story_body">
 <p>
Valve's announcement this week of <a class='gslink' href='/news/valve-reveals-steamos-6414851'>Steam OS</a> and <a class='gslink' href='/news/valve-reveals-steam-machines-6414959'>Steam Machines</a> has caught the eye of Xbox One maker Microsoft. 
<div class="embscreen">
                                <a href="http://www.gamespot.com/pages/image_viewer/index.php?single=1&path=2011%2F11%2Fmicrosoft_logo_57573_screen.jpg&blog=1"rel="popup:imageviewer nofollow">
                                <img class="thumb" src="http://image.gamespotcdn.net/gamespot/images/2011/11/microsoft_logo_57573_embed.jpg" alt="" /></a></div>
</p><p>
Speaking with <a href="http://www.eurogamer.net/articles/2013-09-26-phil-harrison-on-xbox-one-digital-is-an-unstoppable-force">Eurogamer</a>, corporate vice president Phil Harrison said Microsoft will keep a close eye on Valve as the Portal studio pushes into the living room with its new technology.
</p><p>
 "The announcement was only made last night so I'm still studying all the facts Valve has released. But Valve is a very impressive company, and obviously we're going to be watching what they do with great interest," Harrison said. 
</p><p>
For Harrison, Valve's eagerness to move into the living room with Steam Machines speaks to an interest gamers continue to have in console-based experiences. 
</p><p>
"But it actually goes back to an earlier question. I think the death of the video game console was prematurely announced," Harrison said. "Clearly there is a lot of excitement around gaming in the living room on the biggest screen in the house, oftentimes connected to a great sound system and creating that real intensely high-quality game experience with a very powerful CPU and a very powerful GPU."
</p><p>
"Our point of view, clearly, is that Xbox One is the best incarnation of that, but competition is good!" he added.
</p><p>
Valve has a third announcement for this week planned for Friday, September 27, at 1 p.m. EDT. The developer has teased that this announcement <a class='gslink' href='/news/valve-teases-controller-announcement-6414978'>may be related to a proprietary controller</a>.
</p><p>
<div class="video_embed" style="width:480px;"><iframe width="480" height="270" src="http://www.gamespot.com/videoembed/6414971&mapp=editorial&ads=preroll&onsite=1&vidSize=480" frameborder="0" webkitAllowFullScreen mozallowfullscreen allowFullScreen></iframe><div class="video_details"><ul class="video_actions">
                                    <li class="comment first"><a href="/the-orange-box/videos/gamespot-breaking-news-steam-machines-6414971/#generic_comments">Comment<span class="surplus"> on this video</span></a></li><li class="hd"><a href="/the-orange-box/videos/gamespot-breaking-news-steam-machines-6414971/?hd=1"><span>Watch <span class="surplus">this video </span>in </span>High Def</a></li></ul></div></div>
</p> <br/><p><a href="/tags/xboxone">&rarr; More coverage of XBOXONE on GameSpot.com</a></p>
 </div>
 <div class="authorByline authorBylineLarge ">
    <a href="http://www.gamespot.com/users/eddienoteddy/"> <img src="http://image.gamespotcdn.net/gamespot/shared/authors/eddie-makuch-2_100.jpg" class="headShotBig" alt="Eddie Makuch" />
 </a>   <div class="wrap">
 <address>By  <a href="http://www.gamespot.com/users/eddienoteddy/">
 Eddie Makuch</a>, News Editor  </address>
